<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<section xml:id="ch1-sec1" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Vectors and Linear Combinations</title>

  <introduction>
    <p>This section reviews vectors in <m>\mathbb{R}^n</m>, linear combinations, and span.</p>
  </introduction>

  <subsection xml:id="ch1-sec1-defs">
    <title>Basic Definitions</title>
    <p>A vector in <m>\mathbb{R}^n</m> is an ordered <m>n</m>-tuple <m>(x_1,\ldots,x_n)</m>. Vector addition and scalar multiplication are defined componentwise.</p>

    <definition xml:id="def-linear-combination">
      <statement>
        <p>Given vectors <m>v_1,\ldots,v_k \in \mathbb{R}^n</m> and scalars <m>c_1,\ldots,c_k \in \mathbb{R}</m>, a <em>linear combination</em> of the vectors is <m>c_1 v_1 + \cdots + c_k v_k</m>.</p>
      </statement>
    </definition>

    <example xml:id="ex-basic-combo">
      <statement>
        <p>With <m>v_1=(1,0,2)</m>, <m>v_2=(0,1,-1)</m>, and <m>c_1=3</m>, <m>c_2=-2</m>, the linear combination is <m>3v_1-2v_2=(3,-2,8)</m>.</p>
      </statement>
    </example>
  </subsection>

  <subsection xml:id="ch1-sec1-span">
    <title>Span</title>
    <definition xml:id="def-span">
      <statement>
        <p>The <em>span</em> of <m>\{v_1,\ldots,v_k\}</m> is <m>\operatorname{span}\{v_1,\ldots,v_k\}=\{c_1 v_1+\cdots+c_k v_k \mid c_i\in\mathbb{R}\}</m>.</p>
      </statement>
    </definition>
    <p>Geometrically, the span is the smallest subspace containing the vectors.</p>
  </subsection>

  <subsection xml:id="ch1-sec1-linind">
    <title>Linear Independence</title>
    <definition xml:id="def-lin-indep">
      <statement>
        <p>Vectors <m>v_1,\ldots,v_k</m> are <em>linearly independent</em> if <m>c_1 v_1+\cdots+c_k v_k=0</m> implies <m>c_1=\cdots=c_k=0</m>.</p>
      </statement>
    </definition>
    <p>A quick test: place the vectors as columns of a matrix <m>A</m>. If <m>\operatorname{rank}(A)=k</m>, then they are independent.</p>
  </subsection>

  <exercises xml:id="ch1-sec1-exs">
    <exercise xml:id="ch1-sec1-ex1">
      <statement>
        <p>Let <m>v_1=(1,2,0)</m>, <m>v_2=(0,1,1)</m>, <m>v_3=(1,3,1)</m>. Determine whether <m>\{v_1,v_2,v_3\}</m> is linearly independent.</p>
      </statement>
    </exercise>
    <exercise xml:id="ch1-sec1-ex2">
      <statement>
        <p>Describe <m>\operatorname{span}\{(1,0,0),(0,1,0)\}</m> in <m>\mathbb{R}^3</m> geometrically.</p>
      </statement>
    </exercise>
  </exercises>
</section>
